Netherlands Replaces Spain at Top of FIFA Soccer Rankings; Germany Third

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-08-24T11:23:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-24/netherlands-replaces-spain-at-top-of-fifa-soccer-rankings-germany-third.html
The Netherlands has replaced  Spain 
at the top of soccer governing body FIFA’s  world rankings .  Spain, which beat the Dutch 1-0 in last year’s  World Cup 
final, drops to second after an exhibition-match loss to  Italy .  Germany  is third, followed by  England , which rises two
spots. Uruguay is  South America ’s top side, in fifth, after
winning the  Copa America .  Brazil  falls two places to sixth.  To contact the editor on this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 